headline: Robinhood Soars To High As Trump Bitcoin Rally Fuels Earnings Boom
summary: Robinhood stomped past earnings estimates for the fourth quarter on Wednesday as revenue more than doubled.  "Q4 was a record-breaking quarter that caps off a record-setting year in 2024," said Robinhood CFO Jason Warnick in an earnings release.  For Q4, Robinhood posted EPS of $1.01, crushing FactSet consensus views for 42 cents.
